narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: get to learn about the discovery of the ribosome's structure from the guy who actually discovered it. Weaknesses: Yong needs to do more of the teaching, Steitz uses handouts that are hardly legible.

I wished the lecture could be a bit more updated on more recent advances instead of teaching the technology in the history. Learning how these evolve to nowadays is important, but I felt more could have been focused on newer techniques.
